WEBVTT

1
00:02:27.981 --> 00:02:29.357
- Excuse me.
- Yeah?

2
00:02:29.649 --> 00:02:34.487
I'm looking for a mechanic.
Anybody here fit that description?

3
00:02:34.696 --> 00:02:38.116
I might be able to help you.
What do you need?

4
00:02:38.324 --> 00:02:43.038
I need it fixed right away. I need
someone who knows what they're doing.

5
00:02:43.246 --> 00:02:45.999
I'm not that busy.
So. what's the problem?

6
00:02:46.291 --> 00:02:51.212
I'm not sure. Maybe you ought to
get under the hood and check it out.

7
00:02:52.297 --> 00:02:54.674
Yeah. maybe I better.

8
00:03:03.558 --> 00:03:05.643
Looks okay from here.

9
00:03:05.894 --> 00:03:08.646
Great customer service.

10
00:03:10.148 --> 00:03:13.318
Little bit of cleaning.
little bit of paint...

11
00:03:13.526 --> 00:03:16.321
...this place will be ready
for business.

12
00:03:16.529 --> 00:03:19.657
About time for me to play
in the Super Bowl.

13
00:03:19.866 --> 00:03:22.994
Those guys are gonna take you apart.

14
00:03:25.747 --> 00:03:29.125
Okay. we're gonna do it this time!
Ready?

15
00:03:31.503 --> 00:03:33.421
- Okay. ready?
- Yeah!

16
00:03:36.758 --> 00:03:38.468
Hike!

17
00:03:43.390 --> 00:03:45.892
To the left. You can do it. Cut back.

18
00:03:49.813 --> 00:03:51.940
Here it comes.

19
00:03:57.654 --> 00:03:59.114
All right!

20
00:04:02.325 --> 00:04:05.870
Okay. suckers walk. Suckers walk.

21
00:04:06.121 --> 00:04:10.542
Hey. Hey. suckers walk.
Go on. Suckers walk. Come on.

22
00:04:10.834 --> 00:04:12.961
Suckers walk!

23
00:04:16.256 --> 00:04:20.885
- Hey. Frankie. what's that mean?
- It means everything's okay.

24
00:04:21.386 --> 00:04:23.680
So how do you think I did?

25
00:04:23.972 --> 00:04:26.641
Pretty good with the sixth graders.

26
00:04:26.933 --> 00:04:30.854
You really know how to make a guy
feel great. you know that?

27
00:04:31.980 --> 00:04:35.650
What's the matter?
We don't look too happy today?

28
00:04:36.568 --> 00:04:38.695
I'm missing you already.

29
00:04:38.987 --> 00:04:41.573
Pretty soon you'll be so sick
of seeing me...

30
00:04:41.823 --> 00:04:45.243
...you'll pray to have some time
on your own. You know that?

31
00:04:45.493 --> 00:04:48.496
- I don't believe you.
- Yeah. believe it.

32
00:04:51.916 --> 00:04:54.336
Now that's Italian.

33
00:04:58.006 --> 00:04:59.841
- I gotta go.
- No. No.

34
00:05:00.091 --> 00:05:02.761
- I gotta go. Yes. Yes.
- No. No.

35
00:05:03.011 --> 00:05:08.141
So I'm not so good against 10-year-olds?
I should try a different sport?

36
00:05:08.350 --> 00:05:09.559
Yeah. golf.

37
00:05:09.809 --> 00:05:11.561
- Golf?
- Yeah.

38
00:05:11.853 --> 00:05:15.607
- Wanna see my swing?
- I'd like to see you in whites.

39
00:05:16.941 --> 00:05:20.195
- Some swing.
- You see me on the golf course?

40
00:05:20.362 --> 00:05:25.658
You're lucky I have a sense of humour.
I would take that personal.

41
00:05:52.727 --> 00:05:54.437
Time to go to work.

42
00:05:54.688 --> 00:05:56.981
- All right. be good.
- Bye.

43
00:05:59.859 --> 00:06:01.611
Wait a minute.

44
00:06:01.903 --> 00:06:04.239
I got something for you.

45
00:06:04.864 --> 00:06:06.783
What's this?

46
00:06:06.991 --> 00:06:09.577
It's supposed to bring you luck.

47
00:06:12.414 --> 00:06:14.582
It's nice.

48
00:06:15.709 --> 00:06:17.836
Thanks.

49
00:06:19.671 --> 00:06:21.881
I could use it.

50
00:06:39.357 --> 00:06:42.027
- How'd it go. Frank? Good furlough?
- The best.

51
00:06:42.277 --> 00:06:45.447
- Did you see that game?
- I have to admit. I missed it.

52
00:06:45.655 --> 00:06:47.365
- It was awesome.
- Was it?

53
00:06:47.574 --> 00:06:51.202
- Yes. You missed a good one.
- I missed a good one?

54
00:06:51.411 --> 00:06:56.458
- I had more fun than you this weekend.
- I bet you did.

55
00:06:59.044 --> 00:07:01.087
Here you go. Roger.

56
00:07:01.421 --> 00:07:06.134
- How's the diesel running. Jimmy?
- Forget it. It stops. it stalls.

57
00:07:06.426 --> 00:07:09.637
- It don't go.
- You got water in the fuel line.

58
00:07:09.804 --> 00:07:12.057
Open your mouth.

59
00:07:12.265 --> 00:07:14.434
- You sure?
- I'd bet time on it.

60
00:07:14.684 --> 00:07:16.394
- Take it off.
- All right.

61
00:07:19.397 --> 00:07:21.775
I'll see you later. Jimmy.

62
00:07:22.400 --> 00:07:26.363
- I'll give you more starch next time.
- Yeah. do that.

63
00:07:26.613 --> 00:07:29.949
Say hi to the wife.
How you doing there. man?

64
00:07:30.158 --> 00:07:32.535
Frank! What'd you bring me?

65
00:07:32.702 --> 00:07:34.788
Here you go. Go kill yourself.

66
00:07:35.455 --> 00:07:38.583
- I thought you'd bring me a girl.
- I had one...

67
00:07:38.792 --> 00:07:41.836
...but the guards decided to keep her.

68
00:07:42.128 --> 00:07:45.924
I can't depend on you.
Let me ask you something else.

69
00:07:46.132 --> 00:07:48.635
- Did you go see the garage?
- It's beautiful.

70
00:07:49.678 --> 00:07:53.473
- No garage I ever stuck up was beautiful.
- This one is.

71
00:07:53.723 --> 00:07:58.311
Can I tell you something?
I'm getting out soon. I don't come cheap.

72
00:07:58.561 --> 00:08:02.148
But you know I know my way
around cars. You need help. call me.

73
00:08:02.399 --> 00:08:06.820
- I fix them. I don't steal them.
- I was framed.

74
00:08:07.737 --> 00:08:09.280
What? I was framed.

75
00:08:38.810 --> 00:08:41.688
- What is this. Jimmy?
- I don't know. but it's official.

76
00:09:02.000 --> 00:09:04.252
Crack 210.

77
00:09:06.671 --> 00:09:10.342
- On your feet. Leone.
- What do you want?

78
00:09:10.592 --> 00:09:13.345
- Take him.
- What are you doing here?

79
00:09:13.595 --> 00:09:17.265
- You're being transferred.
- Transferred where?

80
00:09:21.144 --> 00:09:25.774
- That's not necessary.
- Step back! He's in our custody now.

81
00:09:26.024 --> 00:09:28.568
You got the wrong guy!

82
00:09:38.578 --> 00:09:40.163
Transferred where?

83
00:09:49.089 --> 00:09:51.591
Talk to me. Where am I going?

84
00:09:54.260 --> 00:09:58.056
- Get in there now!
- Where am I going?

85
00:10:02.018 --> 00:10:03.353
Hey!

86
00:10:03.520 --> 00:10:05.021
Where are we going?

87
00:10:05.355 --> 00:10:08.358
Hey! Talk to me!

88
00:10:55.071 --> 00:10:57.615
Let's go. Leone. Come on!

89
00:10:57.824 --> 00:11:00.827
- Get his ass out here!
- Come on. get out!

90
00:11:02.037 --> 00:11:05.623
- Where the hell are we? I wanna know!
- Shut up!

91
00:11:05.999 --> 00:11:09.586
You got the wrong man!
You made a mistake!

92
00:11:12.047 --> 00:11:14.341
There's no mistake.

93
00:11:18.762 --> 00:11:21.639
Welcome to Gateway. Leone.

94
00:11:21.848 --> 00:11:25.101
- Drumgoole?
- That's Warden Drumgoole. convict.

95
00:11:25.352 --> 00:11:27.729
- Captain.
- Move him!

96
00:11:27.937 --> 00:11:29.105
Move your ass!

97
00:11:29.856 --> 00:11:32.484
Let's go. Come on!

98
00:11:34.903 --> 00:11:39.324
You'll be issued one bar of soap.
two rolls of toilet paper per month.

99
00:11:39.574 --> 00:11:42.285
Somebody steals...
Turn your ass around!

100
00:11:42.535 --> 00:11:47.749
Somebody steals them. or you lose
them. wipe your ass with your shirt.

101
00:11:48.041 --> 00:11:52.212
You have one uniform.
Your number is 5-1-0. Remember it.

102
00:11:53.463 --> 00:11:58.426
This is C-wing. You will eat. shower
and take your yard time with your wing.

103
00:11:58.718 --> 00:12:02.722
There's 6 counts a day. Miss one.
you're in the hole. Miss two...

104
00:12:02.931 --> 00:12:06.226
...I will put you in the house of pain.

105
00:12:07.977 --> 00:12:09.688
Convict...

106
00:12:10.063 --> 00:12:13.817
...two things.
One: I am Meissner.

107
00:12:14.067 --> 00:12:17.404
Two: Never fuck with Meissner.

108
00:12:17.696 --> 00:12:19.906
Inside.

109
00:12:26.413 --> 00:12:30.542
- Sir. what about the cuffs?
- Let him get used to them.

110
00:12:41.886 --> 00:12:44.931
You better watch your back. man!

111
00:13:21.468 --> 00:13:24.054
Come on. guys. Let's go.

112
00:13:40.195 --> 00:13:42.322
Nineteen-one.

113
00:13:50.622 --> 00:13:53.667
Nineteen-one! Crack it!

114
00:13:58.505 --> 00:14:01.841
Oh. yeah. you better not
eyeball me. boy.

115
00:14:02.050 --> 00:14:06.846
How were your accommodations last
night? Like your mama used to do you?

116
00:14:08.306 --> 00:14:11.017
- You did his mama. didn't you?
- Twice.

117
00:14:36.835 --> 00:14:38.044
Hey!

118
00:14:38.294 --> 00:14:41.673
Open the door! You hear me?

119
00:14:42.716 --> 00:14:44.801
Hello. Frank.

120
00:14:45.885 --> 00:14:50.807
In the old days. the warden would've
come down that private passageway...

121
00:14:51.016 --> 00:14:56.271
...to this execution chamber to witness
the putting to death of a criminal.

122
00:14:56.855 --> 00:15:02.402
120 men and 4 women were electrocuted
in that chair before it was retired.

123
00:15:02.652 --> 00:15:07.782
Beautiful. isn't it? When I came here.
it was falling apart. I restored it...

124
00:15:07.991 --> 00:15:13.455
...put it back into working order to
remind me of how things ought to be.

125
00:15:13.747 --> 00:15:16.916
It's nearly five years since you
escaped from Treadmore.

126
00:15:17.167 --> 00:15:21.713
- Time flies when you're having fun.
- In all my years as warden there...

127
00:15:21.921 --> 00:15:26.509
...you're the only one who escaped.
- So I read in the papers.

128
00:15:26.760 --> 00:15:29.971
Yes. you did.
You and your lawyer saw to it...

129
00:15:30.180 --> 00:15:34.559
...that everything made it
into the papers. The media.

130
00:15:34.768 --> 00:15:38.938
Distorting the facts.
making a criminal into a hero...

131
00:15:39.105 --> 00:15:43.610
...and a warden into a criminal.
You took my future away from me.

132
00:15:43.777 --> 00:15:48.990
You and those politicians. They sent
you to Norwood. That's a country club.

133
00:15:49.199 --> 00:15:53.620
I ended up here in Gateway.
the worst shit-hole in the system.

134
00:15:53.828 --> 00:15:56.915
You don't remember. do you?
I asked you.

135
00:15:57.082 --> 00:16:00.210
No. I begged you. Drumgoole.
Do you remember that?

136
00:16:00.377 --> 00:16:05.215
I had two weeks before I was released.
I asked for one hour to visit...

137
00:16:05.382 --> 00:16:09.511
...with that old man before he died.
- I was doing my job.

138
00:16:09.678 --> 00:16:12.305
There's a lot of ways to do your job!

139
00:16:12.514 --> 00:16:16.643
You could've given me an escorted leave.
could've had armed guards.

140
00:16:16.851 --> 00:16:21.231
You broke the law.
You broke the law. and I was punished!

141
00:16:21.648 --> 00:16:26.945
- I got five years. I paid my debt!
- Not to me. But you're going to.

142
00:16:27.362 --> 00:16:30.323
I've only got six months left
on my sentence.

143
00:16:30.532 --> 00:16:34.202
In Gateway.
six months could be a lifetime.

144
00:16:34.411 --> 00:16:38.707
This is hard time. You have no rights
here unless I give them to you.

145
00:16:38.915 --> 00:16:43.211
You feel no pleasure unless
I tell you you can. This is hell...

146
00:16:43.420 --> 00:16:47.215
...and I'm going to give you
the guided tour.

147
00:16:50.593 --> 00:16:55.515
Okay. tough guy. Open your mouth.
Roll your tongue around.

148
00:16:55.724 --> 00:16:58.143
You trying to kiss me. huh?

149
00:16:58.309 --> 00:17:00.729
Let me see your ears.

150
00:17:10.155 --> 00:17:12.782
What are you looking at. asshole?

151
00:17:12.949 --> 00:17:15.243
- You check his nose?
- Checked it.

152
00:17:15.452 --> 00:17:17.287
Good.

153
00:17:21.374 --> 00:17:24.544
This is a delousing chamber.
Don't breathe.

154
00:17:24.711 --> 00:17:30.091
X ylon-profic gas can be harmful to
your lungs. Stand with your legs apart...

155
00:17:30.258 --> 00:17:32.635
...arms out and away from your body.

156
00:17:33.011 --> 00:17:37.349
When I tell you. take a deep breath.
Hold it for 30 seconds.

157
00:17:37.557 --> 00:17:40.310
Start now.

158
00:18:00.163 --> 00:18:02.665
Ten seconds.

159
00:18:12.759 --> 00:18:17.180
Not yet. He can take more.

160
00:18:40.578 --> 00:18:42.330
Braden...

161
00:18:42.539 --> 00:18:48.461
...you'll learn that inmates are physically
more capable than you could imagine.

162
00:18:48.628 --> 00:18:52.007
If you underestimate them...

163
00:18:52.173 --> 00:18:55.176
...it will cost you dearly.

164
00:19:43.433 --> 00:19:45.435
Watch out for the birds.

165
00:19:45.643 --> 00:19:48.897
- What the hell you doing?
- Sorry.

166
00:19:56.196 --> 00:19:59.407
Yo. Billy. get that weight.

167
00:20:18.468 --> 00:20:22.806
Move it. ace. That's my spot.

168
00:20:38.738 --> 00:20:42.826
That's my spot too.

169
00:20:44.411 --> 00:20:47.997
- Any spot that isn't yours?
- Nope. they're all mine.

170
00:20:48.206 --> 00:20:51.626
You wanna use it. you gotta pay.

171
00:20:55.296 --> 00:20:58.299
Not so fast. ace.
I'm not gonna gouge you.

172
00:20:58.466 --> 00:21:03.930
That little thing around your neck.
that'll buy you a spot for the day.

173
00:21:05.557 --> 00:21:10.103
- Put a fucking hole in your heart.
- All right. break it up! Break it up!

174
00:21:10.270 --> 00:21:12.856
I said. break it up! Back off!

175
00:21:13.023 --> 00:21:16.526
Spread 'em. Back off!

176
00:21:16.693 --> 00:21:21.573
- All right. Weber. drop the shank.
- There ain't no shank. Braden.

177
00:21:23.116 --> 00:21:25.535
- All right. let's go.
- You motherfucker!

178
00:21:25.994 --> 00:21:30.331
- Spread 'em. goddamn it.
- You're making a big mistake. asshole.

179
00:21:32.459 --> 00:21:37.339
- You go in the hole for carrying that.
- Where's your witness. your evidence?

180
00:21:37.547 --> 00:21:39.507
Well. where is it?

181
00:21:39.674 --> 00:21:41.217
- He saw it.
- He didn't.

182
00:21:41.426 --> 00:21:46.139
- You saw him carrying the shank. right?
- I didn't see nothing.

183
00:21:46.306 --> 00:21:51.853
- You're making a bad mistake. Braden.
- Get him the fuck out of here!

184
00:21:57.901 --> 00:22:02.864
He would have put that shank in you.
What did you cover for him for?

185
00:22:03.073 --> 00:22:06.242
You got your rules. we got ours.

186
00:22:22.384 --> 00:22:27.597
Hey. hey. hey. I do know the face.
and I do know the name.

187
00:22:27.764 --> 00:22:31.434
Hey. Frank. Frank Leone. right?
Name's Dallas.

188
00:22:31.601 --> 00:22:35.021
I was in Treadmore
right before you busted out.

189
00:22:35.188 --> 00:22:39.275
- You were on A-block. weren't you?
- Yeah. I was on A-block.

190
00:22:39.442 --> 00:22:42.529
- Good memory.
- Treadmore doesn't have an A-block.

191
00:22:42.737 --> 00:22:47.951
- Watch your feet.
- Okay. dig it.

192
00:22:48.159 --> 00:22:51.746
Look. look.
I was there on transfer. man.

193
00:22:51.955 --> 00:22:54.708
Less than two hours.
but I know all about you.

194
00:22:54.916 --> 00:23:00.839
- You're looking at a devoted fan.
- D.T.A.

195
00:23:01.798 --> 00:23:06.553
D.T.A.. okay. What's that. man?

196
00:23:06.720 --> 00:23:11.558
Don't trust anybody.
Words to survive by. Watch your feet.

197
00:23:12.142 --> 00:23:15.562
- D.T.A.
- D.T.A.

198
00:23:15.729 --> 00:23:19.232
You gotta trust somebody.
Let me hip you to the joint.

199
00:23:19.441 --> 00:23:24.070
See this fat tub of shit?
That's Manly. His partner's Wiley.

200
00:23:24.237 --> 00:23:28.658
They're sadistic pigs.
They ain't happy unless they hurt you.

201
00:23:28.867 --> 00:23:33.663
I mean. if the warden wants to put
the boot to you. he uses them.

202
00:23:33.872 --> 00:23:38.376
The black dude in the booth
is Captain Meissner.

203
00:23:38.710 --> 00:23:42.213
Now he runs the guards. okay?
He's one bad dude.

204
00:23:42.380 --> 00:23:44.591
We already met. I gotta do my work.

205
00:23:44.799 --> 00:23:49.512
Okay. Okay. Cool. Cool. man.

206
00:23:50.472 --> 00:23:52.766
So listen. Frank...

207
00:23:52.974 --> 00:23:57.228
...when you decide to make your break.
and I know you will...

208
00:23:57.395 --> 00:24:00.899
...you come talk to me.
You come talk to Dallas.

209
00:24:01.066 --> 00:24:04.652
Okay? Anything you want.
anything you need. man...

210
00:24:04.819 --> 00:24:08.573
...I can get it. Anything.
All right? Okay?

211
00:24:08.782 --> 00:24:08.823
No way. No damn way!

212
00:24:08.823 --> 00:24:11.576
No way. No damn way!

213
00:24:11.743 --> 00:24:15.997
You're always crying about how you
need a man who knows engines.

214
00:24:16.164 --> 00:24:17.874
I brought you the man. Homes.

215
00:24:18.041 --> 00:24:22.462
Look. don't "Homes" me.
The only thing you brought is trouble.

216
00:24:22.671 --> 00:24:26.257
- Come on. Eclipse.
- I heard all about you. Leone.

217
00:24:26.424 --> 00:24:30.637
Whatever is between you and
Drumgoole ain't coming in here.

218
00:24:30.804 --> 00:24:36.643
The boys ain't got no problem with me.
I ain't got no problem with the boys.

219
00:24:40.188 --> 00:24:43.441
Come on. Eclipse.
You're making me look bad.

220
00:24:43.650 --> 00:24:49.698
- I promised the dude a job. You owe me.
- I don't owe you or nobody nothing.

221
00:24:49.906 --> 00:24:54.911
Hey. you! Get your face out of that
motor! Get your face out of there.

222
00:24:55.120 --> 00:24:59.499
You don't know nothing about motors.
Stay away from it! Okay?

223
00:24:59.749 --> 00:25:02.794
It's been a while since I've seen
an old 265 small block.

224
00:25:02.961 --> 00:25:06.756
That's the last time
you're gonna see one in this shop.

225
00:25:06.923 --> 00:25:11.678
Come on. Frank. we can work this out.
We're all gentlemen here.

226
00:25:11.845 --> 00:25:16.766
It's his place. He knows what he
wants. It's okay. Thanks anyway.

227
00:25:20.311 --> 00:25:24.899
Thanks. You made me look beautiful.
I appreciate the endorsement.

228
00:25:25.066 --> 00:25:27.110
Hey. Frank. Hold up. man.

229
00:25:27.944 --> 00:25:32.323
You didn't want this job anyway. man.
Greasy fingers. oil on your clothes...

230
00:25:32.532 --> 00:25:38.121
- Don't worry. I'll take care of you.
- That's what I'm afraid of.

231
00:25:38.288 --> 00:25:41.916
- All right?
- Prison joke.

232
00:25:42.125 --> 00:25:45.670
I lost my watch. Why don't you give me
a hand looking for it.

233
00:25:45.837 --> 00:25:48.298
Roll your ass on out of here. man.

234
00:25:48.465 --> 00:25:53.345
Officer Vazquez. you ought to
put on a few pounds. You look frail.

235
00:25:53.511 --> 00:25:59.601
Frank. I meant what I said. I'm gonna
get you something good. easy. cool.

236
00:26:00.018 --> 00:26:05.231
- You're gonna love it.
- Shut up. Get inside. Shut up. Inside!

237
00:26:10.695 --> 00:26:13.907
Here's your shit from Norwood. Leone.

238
00:26:18.078 --> 00:26:21.373
All right. Lock in!

239
00:26:34.010 --> 00:26:36.262
Problem?

240
00:26:37.931 --> 00:26:40.725
No. I got no problems.

241
00:26:45.939 --> 00:26:48.066
I wanna know what's going on.

242
00:26:48.274 --> 00:26:52.320
All I know is that he's in
the general population...

243
00:26:52.487 --> 00:26:57.367
I don't give a damn about the general
population! I wanna know about Frank.

244
00:26:57.534 --> 00:27:00.745
- I'm not leaving...
- Calm down. He's all right.

245
00:27:00.912 --> 00:27:05.208
He was a model prisoner at Norwood.
Why bring him here?

246
00:27:05.417 --> 00:27:08.378
Routine transfer.

247
00:27:17.595 --> 00:27:19.389
- Hey. Frank?
- What?

248
00:27:19.597 --> 00:27:21.266
Hey. man.

249
00:27:22.809 --> 00:27:26.688
- It's hot in here. man.
- I know. But at least it's easy.

250
00:27:26.896 --> 00:27:30.608
I know. man.
I'm sorry. I didn't do too good.

251
00:27:30.817 --> 00:27:35.113
Walk with me. I gotta show you
something. It's important.

252
00:27:35.280 --> 00:27:37.866
- No. Here. you try.
- No. Come on. man.

253
00:27:38.033 --> 00:27:40.910
- You'll like it.
- I'm not into hard labour.

254
00:27:41.077 --> 00:27:46.332
- It's cool. It's easy.
- Okay. There. I'm burnt out. Come on.

255
00:27:46.541 --> 00:27:49.127
Come on. you're gonna love this.

256
00:27:50.253 --> 00:27:52.922
Watch the steam. Frank.

257
00:27:57.719 --> 00:28:01.348
I got these off this old trustee.
He did the plumbing here.

258
00:28:01.556 --> 00:28:05.894
Everybody thought he was a nut.
Doesn't mean he wasn't smart.

259
00:28:06.603 --> 00:28:09.481
- Come on. hurry up.
- All right. cool.

260
00:28:10.231 --> 00:28:15.278
The tunnels under every cellblock.
they lead to the steam plant. okay?

261
00:28:15.487 --> 00:28:18.865
I go out across the steam lines.
Dig this.

262
00:28:19.032 --> 00:28:24.204
I shimmy. okay? Across the
steam pipes to the sally port. okay?

263
00:28:24.412 --> 00:28:28.958
Over there. there's trucks coming
and going. I wait for my time...

264
00:28:29.250 --> 00:28:34.422
...l'm on a truck that's leaving.
I'm dearly departing Dallas. man. Huh?

265
00:28:35.674 --> 00:28:40.345
You're the doctor. Operate.
I want your professional opinion.

266
00:28:40.512 --> 00:28:45.475
Let's run it backwards. I see these
trucks. They stop running at 9:00.

267
00:28:45.725 --> 00:28:50.814
At 9:00. the tower guards are at full
staff and all the inmates are awake.

268
00:28:50.980 --> 00:28:56.152
Before you go 10 feet. every con in the
joint knows you're gone. And this thing...

269
00:28:56.319 --> 00:28:59.030
...this shimmy?
- Shimmy slide.

270
00:28:59.197 --> 00:29:03.493
You're gonna shimmy slide across
200 yards of steam pipe...

271
00:29:03.660 --> 00:29:05.912
...running at 160 degrees
and get away with it?

272
00:29:06.079 --> 00:29:11.501
You try. they'll change your name from
Departing Dallas to Deep-Fried Dallas.

273
00:29:16.131 --> 00:29:19.009
- Just a thought. man.
- The thought that counts.

274
00:29:19.175 --> 00:29:23.555
- I got a plane to catch. Thanks a lot.
- Hey. Dallas?

275
00:29:24.097 --> 00:29:26.433
You got a cigarette?

276
00:29:28.101 --> 00:29:31.604
It's my last one. Here.
Go ahead. Finish that.

277
00:29:31.813 --> 00:29:35.400
It ain't much.
but it's the thought that counts. right?

278
00:29:56.296 --> 00:30:01.384
Last call. Mess hall. last call.
Mess. coming up.

279
00:30:04.262 --> 00:30:09.351
Looks like some delicious garbage
stew. Just like Mom used to make.

280
00:30:09.517 --> 00:30:12.103
That's why I shot her.

281
00:30:12.979 --> 00:30:17.067
- Can I have some gravy. please?
- You want some gravy?

282
00:30:17.233 --> 00:30:20.528
- Here's your gravy.
- You got it all over my food.

283
00:30:20.737 --> 00:30:22.572
- Move!
- What's your problem?

284
00:30:22.781 --> 00:30:25.992
- Nothing. Move it!
- What's that kid's story?

285
00:30:26.159 --> 00:30:27.827
In for murder.

286
00:30:28.036 --> 00:30:31.956
Claims he was just in the wrong place
at the wrong time.

287
00:30:32.165 --> 00:30:37.253
Waiting while his buddy bought beer.
Didn't know the guy was packing heat.

288
00:30:37.420 --> 00:30:41.841
Two guys dead. Kid's doing
the Big Bitch now: Double life.

289
00:30:42.008 --> 00:30:45.720
He'll make parole when he's about 400.

290
00:30:45.929 --> 00:30:50.975
Move it!
What are you. a slow study or what?

291
00:30:51.184 --> 00:30:52.227
Screw that guy.

292
00:30:53.895 --> 00:30:57.524
So I didn't get a chance
to make the reservation...

293
00:30:57.732 --> 00:31:00.944
...so why don't we get a seat
over there.

294
00:31:02.320 --> 00:31:04.531
- What are you doing?
- Taking this.

295
00:31:04.739 --> 00:31:09.869
- Why don't you go take something else?
- I'll throw you through this table.

296
00:31:10.036 --> 00:31:12.622
- Want some cake?
- Are you chumping off on me?

297
00:31:12.789 --> 00:31:14.541
- Not hungry. Want this?
- Who are you?

298
00:31:14.708 --> 00:31:16.209
Nobody. Here.

299
00:31:18.211 --> 00:31:23.883
- I'm on a diet. This spot taken?
- Why don't you stand up to that dirtbag?

300
00:31:24.092 --> 00:31:27.095
Shut up.
He just saved you a lot of healing.

301
00:31:27.887 --> 00:31:29.848
What's your name?

302
00:31:30.015 --> 00:31:33.768
Why does anybody need a name
in a joint like this?

303
00:31:33.977 --> 00:31:36.062
Helps when you get mail.

304
00:31:36.646 --> 00:31:40.275
Oh. yeah. I need a name?
They call me Killer.

305
00:31:40.483 --> 00:31:45.488
That's original. Did you think that up.
or did someone give you a hand with it?

306
00:31:45.697 --> 00:31:48.992
- I call myself what I want. okay?
- Okay.

307
00:31:49.159 --> 00:31:53.580
Killer. this is Dallas. I'm Frank.
Dallas. what do you think this is here?

308
00:31:53.747 --> 00:31:56.833
- Wanna give me an idea?
- These might be peas.

309
00:31:57.000 --> 00:32:00.045
They might not.
They might be toxic waste.

310
00:32:00.337 --> 00:32:02.380
Who cares? It's all crap.

311
00:32:02.714 --> 00:32:08.762
- Eat vegetables to grow big and strong.
- Stick your vegetables. Nobody asked.

312
00:32:08.928 --> 00:32:12.932
We got 325 other killers in here.
Most. unlike you. live up to it.

313
00:32:13.099 --> 00:32:17.604
Put your leg in the aisle.
Be ready to move.

314
00:32:17.812 --> 00:32:21.649
Hey. nobody tells me
to do nothing. all right?

315
00:32:47.592 --> 00:32:53.765
You always gotta be ready to move first.
You just might make it to first base.

316
00:32:55.266 --> 00:32:59.604
First base.
There's a name for him. huh?

317
00:33:08.863 --> 00:33:11.366
- It's good to be outside.
- It's cold.

318
00:33:11.574 --> 00:33:14.619
It's not that bad.
It's good to keep moving.

319
00:33:14.786 --> 00:33:20.125
How come you got this up attitude?
How can you be up in this joint?

320
00:33:20.333 --> 00:33:24.963
It's a mindset. Your body has to
be in here. but your brain doesn't.

321
00:33:25.171 --> 00:33:28.550
As long as you keep moving.
you don't become a piece of this place.

322
00:33:28.758 --> 00:33:30.927
- What's that. like. guru stuff?
- Yeah.

323
00:33:31.094 --> 00:33:34.848
- Maybe I should become a guru.
- You getting sarcastic?

324
00:33:35.765 --> 00:33:38.518
Fucking birds.

325
00:33:40.645 --> 00:33:44.065
Fucking birds don't eat in the rain.

326
00:33:44.274 --> 00:33:50.280
- Yeah. well. they'll come back.
- You save your bread for me tomorrow?

327
00:33:50.488 --> 00:33:53.408
Yeah. sure.
Put that on your list. okay?

328
00:33:53.616 --> 00:33:55.785
Thanks.

329
00:33:55.994 --> 00:33:59.622
Why you talking crazy. man?
It's a waste of time.

330
00:33:59.789 --> 00:34:02.792
To you. it's a waste.
To him. it's all he's got.

331
00:34:03.001 --> 00:34:06.463
That's more than you got.
In here. you gotta respect that.

332
00:34:06.671 --> 00:34:11.676
You don't get much. and what you got.
you gotta protect. You know that?

333
00:34:11.885 --> 00:34:15.555
You don't know nothing yet.
Come on. let's run.

334
00:34:22.187 --> 00:34:24.314
- Come on. Frank.
- Bitch. bitch. bitch.

335
00:34:24.522 --> 00:34:28.651
I'm gonna get wet.
Send you my laundry bills.

336
00:34:38.578 --> 00:34:41.623
Feel something. Leone?

337
00:34:43.500 --> 00:34:46.378
Wanna play? They're a man short.

338
00:34:54.719 --> 00:34:57.681
Hey! I'm talking to you!

339
00:34:59.140 --> 00:35:04.688
Hey. punk! When you gonna paint your
nails and answer to the name "bitch"?

340
00:35:05.522 --> 00:35:12.195
- You got a big mouth. Keep it shut.
- You fucker. I'll tear your ass off!

341
00:35:12.654 --> 00:35:17.534
You wanna play? We'll play.
You talk too much. Let's play.

342
00:35:17.701 --> 00:35:22.872
Goddamn right we'll play. You
and I'll play later. you little fuck.

343
00:35:36.678 --> 00:35:42.934
You want more. Leone? We got more
for you. Come on. Come on.

344
00:35:46.229 --> 00:35:48.815
- Stay down!
- That's a cheap shot!

345
00:35:53.945 --> 00:35:58.658
- What kind of game is this?
- This ain't no game. This is a lesson.

346
00:36:19.012 --> 00:36:20.680
- Got something to say?
- Yeah.

347
00:36:20.889 --> 00:36:22.932
- Say it! Say it!
- First down!

348
00:36:23.099 --> 00:36:27.812
Fuck you. That's your last one!
You're dead. Leone!

349
00:36:27.979 --> 00:36:31.441
You'll never last the fucking game!

350
00:36:47.207 --> 00:36:50.460
Get in there. hit him.
Come on. get in there.

351
00:36:51.419 --> 00:36:53.296
Set!

352
00:36:53.463 --> 00:36:58.134
Hut-one. Hut-two. Hut-three.

353
00:37:21.241 --> 00:37:23.827
I'll beat you up. man.

354
00:37:36.172 --> 00:37:38.383
Frank!

355
00:37:52.147 --> 00:37:54.649
Hut-one. Hut-two. Hut-three.

356
00:38:06.703 --> 00:38:12.667
Fuck up! Get over on that other team.
That's who you're playing for anyway.

357
00:38:18.131 --> 00:38:21.634
- What took you so long?
- You need the help...

358
00:38:21.885 --> 00:38:25.305
...and I need the exercise.
So call the play.

359
00:38:28.683 --> 00:38:30.852
You're dead. Leone!

360
00:38:44.741 --> 00:38:49.746
- Shit. what hit me?
- F-train. son. F-train.

361
00:39:02.092 --> 00:39:05.220
Don't lay down on me now. Come on.

362
00:39:09.349 --> 00:39:12.060
Come on. Leone.
Come on. you son of a bitch!

363
00:39:12.227 --> 00:39:15.105
All right.
I'm going over tackle on two.

364
00:39:15.313 --> 00:39:16.564
All right. Frank!

365
00:39:17.107 --> 00:39:18.316
Ready.

366
00:39:22.028 --> 00:39:23.363
Set.

367
00:39:23.697 --> 00:39:24.781
You're dead!

368
00:39:25.240 --> 00:39:26.866
Hut-one.

369
00:39:28.535 --> 00:39:29.786
Hut-two.

370
00:39:35.375 --> 00:39:36.501
Go. baby!

371
00:39:40.797 --> 00:39:41.923
Come on. Frank!

372
00:39:57.605 --> 00:39:59.733
We did it!

373
00:40:26.509 --> 00:40:29.262
Hey. come on Wiley. Come on. man!

374
00:40:31.431 --> 00:40:36.061
Next time I want. you give.

375
00:40:45.904 --> 00:40:51.493
Move it. Out. The game is over.
Let's go. You don't listen. do you?

376
00:40:52.452 --> 00:40:56.706
- You okay? Come on. Come on.
- Put him down!

377
00:40:56.873 --> 00:41:02.587
You ain't no doctor. He's on his own.
Get inside.

378
00:41:07.550 --> 00:41:10.303
Real badass. huh?

379
00:41:11.805 --> 00:41:13.973
See you inside. Leone.

380
00:41:15.016 --> 00:41:21.564
Count time. 10 minutes. All inmates
will return to their wings for count.

381
00:41:28.113 --> 00:41:30.156
Let's go. men!

382
00:42:17.454 --> 00:42:19.748
You won't break me.

383
00:42:47.567 --> 00:42:50.320
Still interested in the job?

384
00:42:53.490 --> 00:42:54.741
Yeah. I am.

385
00:43:14.177 --> 00:43:17.847
You sure know your way around
an engine. Who taught you?

386
00:43:18.515 --> 00:43:22.018
This old man named Galleti.

387
00:43:22.185 --> 00:43:24.771
Took me off the street
when I was 14.

388
00:43:24.979 --> 00:43:28.692
Taught me that I could do something
besides hanging out on corners.

389
00:43:28.900 --> 00:43:33.279
- Where is everybody?
- It's quitting time.

390
00:43:33.446 --> 00:43:36.825
- Is that who you broke out for?
- Yeah. I owed him.

391
00:43:36.991 --> 00:43:41.121
Tell me. what put you in the joint
in the first place?

392
00:43:41.287 --> 00:43:45.458
One night these punks broke into the
garage and put a beating on Galleti.

393
00:43:45.667 --> 00:43:48.837
The whole neighbourhood knew about it.
The cops knew.

394
00:43:49.004 --> 00:43:54.050
But these punks were connected.
so the cops didn't do anything. I did.

395
00:43:54.217 --> 00:43:56.594
So after all the smoke had cleared...

396
00:43:56.761 --> 00:44:02.392
...these guys were in the hospital. and I
was doing time for aggravated assault.

397
00:44:02.892 --> 00:44:06.980
- Care to join me in a little contraband?
- Why not?

398
00:44:08.982 --> 00:44:11.776
I can see why they call you Eclipse.

399
00:44:11.985 --> 00:44:15.655
- I do block a lot of sun. don't I?
- That you do.

400
00:44:15.864 --> 00:44:21.327
I had a guy on the outside that used
to get me good Havanas. Not this crap.

401
00:44:21.494 --> 00:44:24.247
But someday... Someday.

402
00:44:24.414 --> 00:44:26.916
Yeah. someday.

403
00:44:27.625 --> 00:44:31.254
- That's not bad.
- At least they're cheap.

404
00:44:34.466 --> 00:44:37.719
Eclipse. what do you
got hiding back there?

405
00:44:38.762 --> 00:44:40.138
That's my baby.

406
00:44:43.641 --> 00:44:47.937
- Good bodywork.
- Call this here vehicle Maybelline.

407
00:44:48.104 --> 00:44:50.648
- Hello. Maybelline.
- This is my baby.

408
00:44:50.815 --> 00:44:52.442
Nice.

409
00:44:55.070 --> 00:44:58.365
There it is. '65 Ford Mustang V8.

410
00:44:58.531 --> 00:45:01.451
Two eighty-nine. with 225 horsepower.

411
00:45:01.659 --> 00:45:05.455
- When did you last turn her over?
- She's been dead for 15 years.

412
00:45:05.663 --> 00:45:11.127
Couple guys tried to get her going
and couldn't. I'm a body man myself.

413
00:45:11.294 --> 00:45:14.422
- Mind if I give it a try?
- It's a dead issue.

414
00:45:17.008 --> 00:45:20.303
Nothing's dead around here
until it's buried.

415
00:45:24.808 --> 00:45:27.560
Save the headstone. man.

416
00:45:27.769 --> 00:45:30.730
Easy. easy...

417
00:48:09.305 --> 00:48:14.060
Eclipse. Nothing's dead till
it's buried. Did I tell you that?

418
00:48:18.273 --> 00:48:20.567
I love it!

419
00:48:22.193 --> 00:48:22.318
- A toast. Let's do the poem. all right?
- What poem?

420
00:48:22.318 --> 00:48:25.947
- A toast. Let's do the poem. all right?
- What poem?

421
00:48:26.698 --> 00:48:29.409
- The poem.
- It's a jailhouse poem.

422
00:48:29.576 --> 00:48:32.203
- Something we all wrote.
- Excuse me.

423
00:48:34.497 --> 00:48:38.626
When we're in a sober mood
We worry. work and think

424
00:48:38.835 --> 00:48:43.006
When we're in a drunken mood
We gamble. play and drink

425
00:48:43.173 --> 00:48:47.469
But when our moods are over
When our time has come to pass

426
00:48:47.677 --> 00:48:52.807
We hope they bury us upside down
So the warden can kiss our ass

427
00:48:52.974 --> 00:48:55.018
- Amen!
- I like that.

428
00:48:55.185 --> 00:48:58.146
- You like that. huh?
- It's a little catchy.

429
00:49:00.357 --> 00:49:03.985
This is the best.
I mean. this is good. man.

430
00:49:04.194 --> 00:49:07.113
- What's wrong. man?
- Nothing.

431
00:49:08.448 --> 00:49:13.578
I wouldn't smoke around this. but
it tastes as good as any dollar wine.

432
00:49:13.745 --> 00:49:15.872
Check. please.

433
00:49:17.040 --> 00:49:19.876
Wait.
When my moods are over

434
00:49:20.043 --> 00:49:22.837
And my...
That's not it. Wait a minute.

435
00:49:24.547 --> 00:49:27.884
You married.
or thinking about it. or what?

436
00:49:28.093 --> 00:49:31.638
Are you proposing to me?
You're not my type.

437
00:49:31.805 --> 00:49:34.140
- No. I'm not married.
- Not married?

438
00:49:34.307 --> 00:49:40.647
- Plan to get married when you get out?
- Yeah. that's the plan.

439
00:49:40.855 --> 00:49:45.443
- You know. I had this really nice girl.
- Yeah?

440
00:49:45.610 --> 00:49:48.405
She was nice. And we were in love.

441
00:49:48.905 --> 00:49:52.325
And we started talking
about getting married.

442
00:49:52.492 --> 00:49:56.830
She's got three brothers. like.
about 1 percent retarded. these guys.

443
00:49:57.038 --> 00:49:59.165
They throw a beating on me.

444
00:49:59.582 --> 00:50:02.460
Some guys don't appreciate romance.

445
00:50:02.627 --> 00:50:05.088
Don't take it personal.

446
00:50:05.255 --> 00:50:10.093
She wrote me for a while.
Then it just stopped.

447
00:50:10.260 --> 00:50:15.515
That's when it hit me: I ain't
ever gonna be with a girl again.

448
00:50:15.682 --> 00:50:20.353
I'm gonna end up like Eclipse.
kissing pictures in magazines.

449
00:50:20.562 --> 00:50:23.648
There's so many things I ain't done.

450
00:50:23.815 --> 00:50:27.694
- I ain't never learned how to drive.
- What?

451
00:50:27.861 --> 00:50:31.031
I ain't never learned
how to drive a car.

452
00:50:34.117 --> 00:50:38.788
I hope we don't get a speeding ticket.
I'd hate to end up in jail.

453
00:50:38.997 --> 00:50:44.461
Don't be a wise guy. You wanna learn
to drive? This is the best I can do.

454
00:50:44.669 --> 00:50:49.049
Okay. Now cut it sharp.
That's it. All right.

455
00:50:49.215 --> 00:50:54.471
Hang a left on 42nd Street. We'll go
to Broadway and check out the action.

456
00:50:54.637 --> 00:50:57.432
Broadway?
We're doing circles in a garage.

